{
 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Fase 5: Modelado ML — Predicción de Precios de Laptops\n",
    "## Entrenamiento y evaluación de modelos de regresión con PySpark ML\n",
    "\n",
    "**Origen:** `abfss://curated@stgabritenreiroprueba.dfs.core.windows.net/`  \n",
    "**Objetivo:** Predecir el precio de una laptop en base a sus especificaciones técnicas.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Modelos a comparar:**\n",
    "1. `LinearRegression` — Baseline lineal\n",
    "2. `RandomForestRegressor` — Modelo ensemble con bagging\n",
    "3. `GBTRegressor` — Gradient Boosted Trees (boosting)\n",
    "\n",
    "**Métricas de evaluación:** RMSE, MAE, R²"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from pyspark.sql import functions as F\n",
    "from pyspark.ml.feature import StringIndexer, OneHotEncoder, VectorAssembler, StandardScaler\n",
    "from pyspark.ml.regression import LinearRegression, RandomForestRegressor, GBTRegressor\n",
    "from pyspark.ml import Pipeline\n",
    "from pyspark.ml.evaluation import RegressionEvaluator\n",
    "\n",
    "# Storage account (hardcoded default, override via pipeline parameters if needed)\n",
    "STORAGE_ACCOUNT = 'stgabritenreiroprueba'\n",
    "\n",
    "# Try to override with pipeline parameter\n",
    "try:\n",
    "    from notebookutils import mssparkutils\n",
    "    param = mssparkutils.notebook.getParameter('storage_account')\n",
    "    if param and param.strip():\n",
    "        STORAGE_ACCOUNT = param.strip()\n",
    "except Exception:\n",
    "    pass\n",
    "\n",
    "CURATED_PATH = f'abfss://curated@{STORAGE_ACCOUNT}.dfs.core.windows.net/'\n",
    "\n",
    "assert CURATED_PATH, 'Path cannot be empty'\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f'Storage: {STORAGE_ACCOUNT}')\n",
    "print(f'Curated: {CURATED_PATH}')\n",
    "print(f'Spark version: {spark.version}')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## 1. Carga de datos\n",
    "\n",
    "Usamos la capa Curated porque ya tiene los datos limpios, deduplicados y con\n",
    "las columnas derivadas necesarias (CPU_Brand, GPU_Brand, Screen_Category,\n",
    "Has_Dedicated_GPU)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "df_curated = spark.read.parquet(CURATED_PATH)\n",
    "\n",
    "total_rows = df_curated.count()\n",
    "print(f'Filas cargadas: {total_rows:,}')\n",
    "print(f'Columnas: {len(df_curated.columns)}')\n",
    "df_curated.printSchema()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## 2. Preparación de datos para ML\n",
    "\n",
    "### Selección de features\n",
    "\n",
    "Incluimos todas las columnas que tienen relación con las especificaciones\n",
    "técnicas del laptop y que están disponibles ANTES de conocer el precio.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Columnas excluidas (con justificación):\n",
    "\n",
    "| Columna | Razón de exclusión |\n",
    "|---|---|\n",
    "| `Price` | Target variable (lo que queremos predecir) |\n",
    "| `Price_per_RAM_GB` | Data leak — contiene el precio en su fórmula |\n",
    "| `Price_per_Storage_GB` | Data leak — contiene el precio en su fórmula |\n",
    "| `Company` | Se incluye como feature categórica |\n",
    "| `TypeName` | Demasiados valores únicos (high cardinality), no generaliza bien |\n",
    "| `Cpu` | Redundante con CPU_Brand (texto libre vs categoría) |\n",
    "| `Gpu` | Redundante con GPU_Brand (texto libre vs categoría) |\n",
    "| `ScreenResolution` | Redundante con X_res, Y_res, ppi |\n",
    "| `Storage_Type` | Redundante con Storage_Category |\n",
    "| `Storage_Category` | Se incluye como feature categórica |\n",
    "| `Dedicated_Gpu` | Redundante con Has_Dedicated_GPU (misma info) |\n",
    "| `ppi` | Derivada de X_res, Y_res e Inches — multicolinealidad |\n",
    "| `X_res` | Se incluye como feature numérica |\n",
    "| `Y_res` | Se incluye como feature numérica |\n",
    "\n",
    "### Features seleccionadas:\n",
    "\n",
    "**Numéricas:** Ram_GB, Inches, Weight_kg, Total_Storage_GB, SSD, HDD,\n",
    "TouchScreen, Ips, X_res, Y_res\n",
    "\n",
    "**Categóricas:** CPU_Brand, GPU_Brand, Screen_Category, OpSys,\n",
    "Storage_Category, Company, Has_Dedicated_GPU"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Features numéricas — especificaciones técnicas cuantificables\n",
    "numeric_features = [\n",
    "    'Ram_GB',           # Memoria RAM (GB)\n",
    "    'Inches',           # Tamaño de pantalla\n",
    "    'Weight_kg',        # Peso del laptop\n",
    "    'Total_Storage_GB', # Almacenamiento total\n",
    "    'SSD',              # Capacidad SSD\n",
    "    'HDD',              # Capacidad HDD\n",
    "    'TouchScreen',      # 1=táctil, 0=no\n",
    "    'Ips',              # 1=panel IPS, 0=no\n",
    "    'X_res',            # Resolución horizontal\n",
    "    'Y_res',            # Resolución vertical\n",
    "]\n",
    "\n",
    "# Features categóricas — atributos cualitativos del producto\n",
    "categorical_features = [\n",
    "    'CPU_Brand',        # Intel / AMD / Apple / Other\n",
    "    'GPU_Brand',        # NVIDIA / AMD / Intel / Other\n",
    "    'Screen_Category',  # Compact / Standard / Large / XL\n",
    "    'OpSys',            # Windows / macOS / Chrome OS / Linux\n",
    "    'Storage_Category', # SSD Only / HDD Only / Hybrid / etc.\n",
    "    'Company',          # Marca del fabricante\n",
    "    'Has_Dedicated_GPU',# 1=sí, 0=no\n",
    "]\n",
    "\n",
    "# Target variable\n",
    "target_col = 'Price'\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f'Features numéricas ({len(numeric_features)}): {numeric_features}')\n",
    "print(f'Features categóricas ({len(categorical_features)}): {categorical_features}')\n",
    "print(f'Target: {target_col}')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Verificar y manejar valores nulos en las features\n",
    "# Los algoritmos de Spark ML no aceptan nulls en las features\n",
    "# Rellenamos con la mediana para numéricas y 'Unknown' para categóricas\n",
    "\n",
    "# Contar nulos en features seleccionadas\n",
    "null_check = df_curated.select([\n",
    "    F.count(F.when(F.col(c).isNull(), c)).alias(c)\n",
    "    for c in numeric_features + categorical_features + [target_col]\n",
    "])\n",
    "\n",
    "print('Valores nulos en features seleccionadas:')\n",
    "null_check.show(vertical=True)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Imputación de valores nulos\n",
    "# Rellenamos nulos numéricos con 0 (es razonable para SSD/HDD cuando no aplica)\n",
    "# y nulos categóricos con 'Unknown'\n",
    "\n",
    "# Para numéricas: 0 es semánticamente correcto para SSD/HDD cuando no hay ese tipo\n",
    "for col in numeric_features:\n",
    "    df_curated = df_curated.withColumn(\n",
    "        col, F.coalesce(F.col(col), F.lit(0))\n",
    "    )\n",
    "\n",
    "# Para categóricas: 'Unknown' como categoría separada\n",
    "for col in categorical_features:\n",
    "    df_curated = df_curated.withColumn(\n",
    "        col, F.coalesce(F.col(col), F.lit('Unknown'))\n",
    "    )\n",
    "\n",
    "# Filtrar filas sin precio (no sirven para supervised learning)\n",
    "df_ml = df_curated.filter(F.col(target_col).isNotNull())\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f'Filas tras filtrar nulls en Price: {df_ml.count():,}')\n",
    "print(f'Filas eliminadas: {total_rows - df_ml.count():,}')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## 3. Pipeline de preprocesamiento\n",
    "\n",
    "Construimos un pipeline de Spark ML que transforma los datos crudos en un vector\n",
    "de features numéricas apto para los algoritmos de regresión.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Pasos del pipeline:\n",
    "1. **StringIndexer**: Convierte strings categóricos en índices numéricos (0, 1, 2...)\n",
    "2. **OneHotEncoder**: Convierte índices en vectores one-hot para evitar ordenamiento artificial\n",
    "3. **VectorAssembler**: Combina todas las features numéricas + one-hot en un solo vector\n",
    "4. **StandardScaler**: Normaliza las features para que estén en la misma escala\n",
    "   (importante para Linear Regression; los árboles son invariantes a escala)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Paso 1: StringIndexer para cada feature categórica\n",
    "# Convierte 'Intel' -> 0, 'AMD' -> 1, etc.\n",
    "# handleInvalid='keep' asigna un índice especial a categorías no vistas\n",
    "indexers = [\n",
    "    StringIndexer(inputCol=col, outputCol=f'{col}_idx', handleInvalid='keep')\n",
    "    for col in categorical_features\n",
    "]\n",
    "\n",
    "# Paso 2: OneHotEncoder para cada feature indexada\n",
    "# Convierte índice 0 -> [1,0,0], índice 1 -> [0,1,0], etc.\n",
    "# dropLast=False mantiene todas las categorías (importante para árboles)\n",
    "encoders = [\n",
    "    OneHotEncoder(inputCol=f'{col}_idx', outputCol=f'{col}_encoded', dropLast=False)\n",
    "    for col in categorical_features\n",
    "]\n",
    "\n",
    "# Columnas encoded para el assembler\n",
    "encoded_cols = [f'{col}_encoded' for col in categorical_features]\n",
    "\n",
    "# Paso 3: VectorAssembler — junta numéricas + encoded en un solo vector\n",
    "all_feature_cols = numeric_features + encoded_cols\n",
    "\n",
    "assembler = VectorAssembler(\n",
    "    inputCols=all_feature_cols,\n",
    "    outputCol='raw_features'\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Paso 4: StandardScaler — normaliza features a media 0 y varianza 1\n",
    "# Esto beneficia especialmente a Linear Regression\n",
    "scaler = StandardScaler(\n",
    "    inputCol='raw_features',\n",
    "    outputCol='features',\n",
    "    withStd=True,\n",
    "    withMean=True\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f'Total de columnas de entrada al assembler: {len(all_feature_cols)}')\n",
    "print(f'  - Numéricas: {len(numeric_features)}')\n",
    "print(f'  - Categóricas encoded: {len(encoded_cols)}')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## 4. Train/Test Split\n",
    "\n",
    "Dividimos los datos en 80% entrenamiento y 20% test.\n",
    "Usamos una semilla fija (seed=42) para reproducibilidad.\n",
    "\n",
    "El conjunto de test se reserva completamente y NO se usa durante el entrenamiento,\n",
    "para obtener una evaluación honesta del rendimiento del modelo."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Split 80/20 con semilla fija para reproducibilidad\n",
    "train_df, test_df = df_ml.randomSplit([0.8, 0.2], seed=42)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f'Train: {train_df.count():,} filas ({train_df.count()/df_ml.count()*100:.1f}%)')\n",
    "print(f'Test:  {test_df.count():,} filas ({test_df.count()/df_ml.count()*100:.1f}%)')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## 5. Entrenamiento de modelos\n",
    "\n",
    "Entrenamos 3 modelos de regresión para comparar su rendimiento:\n",
    "\n",
    "### 5.1 LinearRegression (Baseline)\n",
    "Modelo lineal simple. Sirve como baseline mínimo: cualquier modelo más complejo\n",
    "debe superarlo. Asume relación lineal entre features y precio.\n",
    "\n",
    "### 5.2 RandomForestRegressor\n",
    "Ensemble de árboles de decisión con bagging. Captura relaciones no lineales\n",
    "e interacciones entre features. Robusto a outliers.\n",
    "\n",
    "### 5.3 GBTRegressor (Gradient Boosted Trees)\n",
    "Ensemble secuencial donde cada árbol corrige los errores del anterior.\n",
    "Suele ser el más preciso de los tres, pero más propenso a overfitting."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# ============================================\n",
    "# MODELO 1: Linear Regression (Baseline)\n",
    "# ============================================\n",
    "# Modelo lineal simple como punto de referencia.\n",
    "# Si los modelos complejos no superan significativamente a este,\n",
    "# significa que la relación features→precio es esencialmente lineal.\n",
    "\n",
    "lr = LinearRegression(\n",
    "    featuresCol='features',\n",
    "    labelCol=target_col,\n",
    "    maxIter=100,\n",
    "    regParam=0.1,        # Regularización L2 para evitar overfitting\n",
    "    elasticNetParam=0.0  # Ridge regression (L2 pura)\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "lr_pipeline = Pipeline(stages=indexers + encoders + [assembler, scaler, lr])\n",
    "lr_model = lr_pipeline.fit(train_df)\n",
    "\n",
    "lr_predictions = lr_model.transform(test_df)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Evaluar\n",
    "lr_rmse = RegressionEvaluator(labelCol=target_col, predictionCol='prediction', metricName='rmse').evaluate(lr_predictions)\n",
    "lr_mae = RegressionEvaluator(labelCol=target_col, predictionCol='prediction', metricName='mae').evaluate(lr_predictions)\n",
    "lr_r2 = RegressionEvaluator(labelCol=target_col, predictionCol='prediction', metricName='r2').evaluate(lr_predictions)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f'=== LINEAR REGRESSION ===')\n",
    "print(f'RMSE: {lr_rmse:.2f} €')\n",
    "print(f'MAE:  {lr_mae:.2f} €')\n",
    "print(f'R²:   {lr_r2:.4f}')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# ============================================\n",
    "# MODELO 2: Random Forest Regressor\n",
    "# ============================================\n",
    "# Ensemble de 100 árboles de decisión con bagging.\n",
    "# Cada árbol ve un subconjunto aleatorio de datos y features.\n",
    "# El promedio de todas las predicciones reduce la varianza.\n",
    "\n",
    "rf = RandomForestRegressor(\n",
    "    featuresCol='features',\n",
    "    labelCol=target_col,\n",
    "    numTrees=100,          # 100 árboles en el ensemble\n",
    "    maxDepth=10,           # Profundidad máxima para controlar overfitting\n",
    "    minInstancesPerNode=5, # Mínimo de muestras por nodo hoja\n",
    "    seed=42\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "rf_pipeline = Pipeline(stages=indexers + encoders + [assembler, scaler, rf])\n",
    "rf_model = rf_pipeline.fit(train_df)\n",
    "\n",
    "rf_predictions = rf_model.transform(test_df)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Evaluar\n",
    "rf_rmse = RegressionEvaluator(labelCol=target_col, predictionCol='prediction', metricName='rmse').evaluate(rf_predictions)\n",
    "rf_mae = RegressionEvaluator(labelCol=target_col, predictionCol='prediction', metricName='mae').evaluate(rf_predictions)\n",
    "rf_r2 = RegressionEvaluator(labelCol=target_col, predictionCol='prediction', metricName='r2').evaluate(rf_predictions)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f'=== RANDOM FOREST ===')\n",
    "print(f'RMSE: {rf_rmse:.2f} €')\n",
    "print(f'MAE:  {rf_mae:.2f} €')\n",
    "print(f'R²:   {rf_r2:.4f}')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# ============================================\n",
    "# MODELO 3: Gradient Boosted Trees (GBT)\n",
    "# ============================================\n",
    "# Ensemble secuencial: cada árbol se entrena para corregir\n",
    "# los errores residuales del ensemble anterior.\n",
    "# learningRate=0.1 controla cuánto contribuye cada árbol.\n",
    "# Suele ser el modelo más preciso pero requiere más tuning.\n",
    "\n",
    "gbt = GBTRegressor(\n",
    "    featuresCol='features',\n",
    "    labelCol=target_col,\n",
    "    maxIter=100,           # Número de árboles (iteraciones)\n",
    "    maxDepth=5,            # Profundidad menor que RF (boosting es más potente)\n",
    "    learningRate=0.1,      # Paso de aprendizaje — más bajo = más estable\n",
    "    subsamplingRate=0.8,   # 80% de datos por árbol (reduce overfitting)\n",
    "    seed=42\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "gbt_pipeline = Pipeline(stages=indexers + encoders + [assembler, scaler, gbt])\n",
    "gbt_model = gbt_pipeline.fit(train_df)\n",
    "\n",
    "gbt_predictions = gbt_model.transform(test_df)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Evaluar\n",
    "gbt_rmse = RegressionEvaluator(labelCol=target_col, predictionCol='prediction', metricName='rmse').evaluate(gbt_predictions)\n",
    "gbt_mae = RegressionEvaluator(labelCol=target_col, predictionCol='prediction', metricName='mae').evaluate(gbt_predictions)\n",
    "gbt_r2 = RegressionEvaluator(labelCol=target_col, predictionCol='prediction', metricName='r2').evaluate(gbt_predictions)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f'=== GRADIENT BOOSTED TREES ===')\n",
    "print(f'RMSE: {gbt_rmse:.2f} €')\n",
    "print(f'MAE:  {gbt_mae:.2f} €')\n",
    "print(f'R²:   {gbt_r2:.4f}')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## 6. Comparación de modelos\n",
    "\n",
    "Comparamos los 3 modelos usando las 3 métricas:\n",
    "\n",
    "- **RMSE** (Root Mean Squared Error): Penaliza más los errores grandes.\n",
    "  En euros: cuánto se desvía en promedio la predicción (con peso en outliers).\n",
    "\n",
    "- **MAE** (Mean Absolute Error): Error absoluto promedio.\n",
    "  En euros: cuánto se equivoca de media el modelo.\n",
    "\n",
    "- **R²** (R-squared): Proporción de varianza explicada.\n",
    "  1.0 = perfecto, 0.0 = no mejor que predecir la media."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Tabla comparativa de los 3 modelos\n",
    "from pyspark.sql import Row\n",
    "\n",
    "results = [\n",
    "    Row(Modelo='Linear Regression', RMSE=round(lr_rmse, 2), MAE=round(lr_mae, 2), R2=round(lr_r2, 4)),\n",
    "    Row(Modelo='Random Forest', RMSE=round(rf_rmse, 2), MAE=round(rf_mae, 2), R2=round(rf_r2, 4)),\n",
    "    Row(Modelo='GBT Regressor', RMSE=round(gbt_rmse, 2), MAE=round(gbt_mae, 2), R2=round(gbt_r2, 4)),\n",
    "]\n",
    "\n",
    "df_results = spark.createDataFrame(results)\n",
    "\n",
    "print('=== COMPARACIÓN DE MODELOS ===')\n",
    "print('')\n",
    "df_results.orderBy(F.desc('R2')).show(truncate=False)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Identificar el mejor modelo por R²\n",
    "best_model = df_results.orderBy(F.desc('R2')).first()['Modelo']\n",
    "print(f'>> Mejor modelo por R²: {best_model}')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Ejemplo de predicciones vs reales del mejor modelo\n",
    "# Mostramos 15 ejemplos para ver cómo se comporta el modelo\n",
    "\n",
    "best_predictions = gbt_predictions  # GBT suele ser el mejor\n",
    "\n",
    "best_predictions.select(\n",
    "    'Company',\n",
    "    'Ram_GB',\n",
    "    'Total_Storage_GB',\n",
    "    'Inches',\n",
    "    'CPU_Brand',\n",
    "    'GPU_Brand',\n",
    "    F.col(target_col).alias('Precio_Real'),\n",
    "    F.round(F.col('prediction'), 2).alias('Precio_Predicho'),\n",
    "    F.round(F.abs(F.col(target_col) - F.col('prediction')), 2).alias('Error_Absoluto')\n",
    ").orderBy(F.desc('Error_Absoluto')) \\\n",
    " .show(15, truncate=False)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## 7. Feature Importance (Importancia de Features)\n",
    "\n",
    "Extraemos la importancia relativa de cada feature en el mejor modelo\n",
    "(Random Forest o GBT). Esto revela qué características del laptop\n",
    "más influyen en su precio.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Por qué importa:** Permite entender los drivers del precio y comunicar\n",
    "insights de negocio: \"¿qué hace que una laptop sea más cara?\""
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Extraer feature importance del modelo GBT\n",
    "# GBTRegressor no tiene featureImportances nativo en todas las versiones,\n",
    "# pero RandomForest sí. Usamos RF para feature importance.\n",
    "\n",
    "# Obtener el modelo RF del pipeline\n",
    "rf_stage = rf_model.stages[-1]  # Último stage es el RandomForestRegressor\n",
    "importances = rf_stage.featureImportances.toArray()\n",
    "\n",
    # Obtener nombres de features del VectorAssembler\n",
